v2.0.9beta La Lisa Edition

New: Custom Report 2 Example.

New: Custom Report 3 Example

New: Barcode scanner feature added to order form. In modern browsers, this needs to enable camera
	and thus to use https. In web.xml, instead of <transport-guarantee>NONE</transport-guarantee>
	use <transport-guarantee>CONFIDENTIAL</transport-guarantee>.
	Also, copy to the Tomcat instance conf directory the self-signed SSL certificate included
	in the war file with the name tcptooldevks.p12. You MUST replace this certificate with the yours.
	
	In server.xml, the proper SSL adapter must be enabled by uncommenting this statement and setting the 
	correct certificate file pathname (conf/tcptooldevks.p12 or the yours):
	
	<Connector SSLEnabled="true" maxThreads="150" port="8443" protocol="org.apache.coyote.http11.Http11NioProtocol">
        <UpgradeProtocol className="org.apache.coyote.http2.Http2Protocol"/>
        <SSLHostConfig>
            <Certificate certificateKeystoreFile="conf/tcptooldevks.p12" certificateKeystorePassword="123456" type="RSA"/>
        </SSLHostConfig>
    </Connector>

Fix: PostgreSQL function soberano."z-fn_ReportData_customReport1_productionAndSales" improperly
	returned inventory item code, and wrongly grouped columns, resulting in bad item day sales. 
	Total item sales in the period was right though.
	
Fix: Inventory recalculation always set process input values to 0. Correction:

	In FUNCTION "soberano"."fn_Stock_change"("stockchangeid" integer) RETURNS "void"
	
	Replace this: newStockUnitValue * CASE WHEN quantity < 0 THEN 0 ELSE abs(quantity) END,
	
	by this: SET "Value" = newStockUnitValue * abs(quantity),
	
	

